    <summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://oss.huaecho.cn/blogimage/2DCOSXAS/cover/cover.png?imageMogr2/format/avif&quot; alt=&quot;2D COS Cover&quot; title=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;50%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Initially developed approximately 30 years ago in NMR spectroscopy,
two-dimensional spectroscopy facilitated the visualization of complex
spectra characterized by numerous overlapping peaks by distributing them
across a second dimension. While NMR remains the predominant technique
in two-dimensional spectroscopy, this approach has been extended to
other forms, proving particularly useful across various spectroscopic
techniques.&lt;/p&gt;</summary>
    
    
    
