  <entry>
    <title>Principles of Powder Diffraction</title>
    <link href="https://www.huaecho.cn/Pattern/Powder-Diffraction/2865233054.html"/>
    <id>https://www.huaecho.cn/Pattern/Powder-Diffraction/2865233054.html</id>
    <published>2020-06-25T03:59:17.000Z</published>
    <updated>2023-07-25T09:28:17.000Z</updated>
    
    
    <summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://oss.huaecho.cn/blogimage/powderdiffraction/therory/cover/powderdiffraction.jpg?imageMogr2/format/avif&quot; alt=&quot;powderdiffraction&quot; title=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;40%&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Powder diffraction is an awesome technique using &lt;em&gt;X-ray&lt;/em&gt;,
&lt;em&gt;neutron&lt;/em&gt;, or &lt;em&gt;electron&lt;/em&gt; diffraction on powder or
microcrystalline samples for structural characterization of materials.
Single crystal analysis is the preferred method for determining crystal
structures, but when suitable single crystals are unavailable, powder
diffraction is an effective alternative. Unlike single crystal analysis,
powder diffraction also provides information on bulk material and
microstructural properties. Nowadays, Powder diffraction continues to be
a crucial tool in the characterization of materials.&lt;/p&gt;</summary>
    
    
    
